Put a large #saucepan{} of water with a pinch of @salt{pinch} on to boil for the
@potato{1}(chopped into 2cm chunks). Cook for ~{20%minutes}.

> TIP: The potato is cooked when you can easily slip a knife through.

When done, drain in a #colander{}. Set aside for ~{2%minutes} to let the steam
escape, then return to the pan off the heat to keep warm.

Put a #frying pan{} on high heat and add the @lamb mince{250%g} (no oil
necessary). Brown the @mince{}, breaking it up with a #wooden spoon{} as it
cooks. Halve, peel and chop the @red onion{1/2}(halved, peeled and chopped into
small chunks). Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated). Once the
mince has browned, drain any excess fat and add the @onion{}. Give it a stir and
lower the heat to medium. Cook for ~{4-5%minutes}.

When the onion is soft, add the garlic and the @shawarma spice mix{1.5%tsp}.
Cook for ~{2%minutes}. Next, add the @tomato passata{1}, @chicken stock pot{1/2}
and the @water{50%ml}. Stir well to dissolve the stock pot and simmer until the
lamb mixture has thickened and reduced by half, ~{10-15%minutes}. Grate the
@mature cheddar cheese{30%g} and pop another large saucepan of water on to boil.
Preheat your #grill{} to its highest setting.

When the potato is cooked and drained, mash with a #potato masher{} and mix
through the @unsalted butter{15%g} (add a splash of milk too, if you have some).
Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Taste the lamb mixture and add more
salt and black pepper if necessary. Spoon the lamb mixture into an
#ovenproof dish{}. Top with the mashed potato, then sprinkle over the cheese.
Pop the dish under your grill until the cheese is golden and bubbly, ~{3%minutes}.

Cook the @Tenderstem broccoli{1%pack} in your pan of boiling water, ~{3-4%minutes}. Drain
in your colander, then season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} to taste.

Share the shepherd's pie between your plates with the broccoli on the side.
Enjoy!